class Solution {
public:
    int accountBalanceAfterPurchase(int purchaseAmount) {
        int roundedAmount = (purchaseAmount + 5) / 10 * 10;
        return 100 - roundedAmount;
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution directly calculates the rounded amount by adding 5 to the purchase amount, then dividing by 10 and multiplying by 10. This effectively rounds the purchase amount to the nearest multiple of 10. It then subtracts this rounded amount from the initial balance of 100 to get the final balance.
